reviewText: Not much singing in the video.
my son is actually learning a lot and enjoys these movies, we don't have cable so I liked getting a bunch of educational shows for cheap!!
My grandson, age 2, loves these videos. He plays at least 1 of them every day.

My brother enjoyed the whole thing, and I rather had fun too!  Bought to replace the Let's Learn ABCS and 123's he had before that got lost. Played perfectly. My brother couldn't wait to watch the whole thing! It was particularly interesting Watching thr Colors one, since I had never watched "Bubble Guppies" before. Great for the children in your life! Has great shows from Team Umizoomi, Blues Clues, Dora, Bubble Guppies, Wonder Pets, etc.
My 4 years old love it

Many hours of learning and entertaining at the same time at a great price. When my son is happy, I am happy!!
These are good for the price but the one on colors only really has two episodes that teach colors the others just talk about coloring. Numbers is a little better, haven't watched letters yet.
My kids are obsessed with this movie combo. I love that it's educational. Some of the episodes are a bit of a reach for their associated theme but overall this is a great product.
Nice to have variety. This was a little 'higher' of a level than the similar 'Kindness' DVD. Very cute coloring page on back of cover insert.
Good, not as much singing as I thought there would be. However, my son loves them.
My son loves this pack of DVDs. He's 3 yrs old and his vocabulary and understanding of the material and concepts covered has been remarkable.

My daughter loves these. She laughs, giggles, & tries her best singing a long. The best part for me as the parent, is you don't have to continuously press play if they want to keep watching. These entertain her endlessly giving me time to get stuff done around the house. Also educational so a definite plus there.

This was a true value pack! Great price, great variety of DVDs and it is very educational. It got my 2 year old interested in colors. He struggled with recognition but now he talks about what his favorite color is!
